<br>
Here goes:<br>
<br>
First. You dont nuke the gnolls. You chain. If you are not a chainer, this camp is not for you, move along to another place :P. Having an enshrouded veil helps immensly here.<br>
<br>
First, you dont fight your way in. Ever. you invis up and run to your camp spot. Only the casters see invis, and they have a smallish agro range. So jsut take your time walking through, look at the mobs, and wait for the raoming casters to move along. If one starts to cast on you, dont loose your head. Thye will cast once or twice before they melee, giving you time to get off a gate. If your gate fails, Then, RUN. :P Most often it wont fail. Actually, most often it wont matter cause you'll make it to your camp spot no problem.<br>
<br>
Now, the first safe spot (no roamers) is the drop down room. Its the easiest of the 2 spots i recomend, and it has more than enough spawns solo till you get to 56/57. Make sure you have lev on, and enter the cave complex. Keep taking rights at every junction untill you enter a long hallway with no gnolls in it. Proceed down teh hallway and you will come to a place where there is a false floor with an illision looking like a floor over it (near a rock). float down and you will be at the end of a hallway. This is your your camp. Everything down there is single pullable, so just bring up the earth pet, DS and BO it, pull, send pet in, sit down and meditate. Chain a pet when ya ahve to, 51 pet needs chainning almost always, 57 can tank the casters and some of the melee's without a chain.<br>
<br>
When ya can take most of the drop down room and you want to move on to bigger and better, proceeded to the LARGE cave in the back of the gnoll complex. Its hard to explain how to get there, so either you'll have explored by then, or you'll have found a map somewheres. Anways, in the middle of the cave is a large rock. Set up your camp ontop of the rock. If you stay on top at 55+, nothing will agro you. From there, you can literally pull the WHOLE room without moving, jsut by bolting stuff. There are like 16 spawns total, so its mass chaos for yourself solo with kei, or with a healing partner. A ton of fun.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps. :P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eloinapyromancer>Eloina Pyromancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 104<br> <font color=#333333>(10/30/02 5:24:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=311.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: JP Gnolls</span><hr size=1> Ok, I'll have to try that.  One more question: why chain rather than nuke?  <br>
