<br>
&quot;why chain rather than nuke&quot;<br>
<br>
I thought the same.<br>
Fought TroJegs on the plateau in SD and was used to have an equiped Voc Air pet (Plate armor + usually even with Gnoll Hide Lariat and a Ykesha weapon) and then keep it alive and nuke.<br>
After 3 to 4 Mobs I was oom and had to med.<br>
With KEI i managed to kill 9 or maybe 10 (depending a bit on the type of TroJegs I got) until respawn.<br>
<br>
Recently I switched to chaining.<br>
First I tried it with Voc Earth and saw a steep increase of kills. Now I can kill 12+ per spawncycle.<br>
GVoc Earth is about the same efficiency but I use this one just for the reason of higher safety (chance of root to stick).<br>
<br>
When I started chaining I also didnt have any clicky BO or DS (but horse and BWS).<br>
Recently I got Bo3-legs and I think that adds a bit to the efficiency (but less than one may think because of long casting time). when I casted new pet I cast cadeau on it, then send it to the mob and then use clicky BO3 and when thats done I use BWS to nuke a bit.<br>
<br>
But in anyway chaining increased the efficiency 33% or more and thats more than just noticable.<br>
<br>
