If at the end of last fight your Pet has more than 20% HPs left you can still use it. (unless you know you will pull a TroJeg Fire *servant* next, here I would propose 30% HPs left, since they can take down 30% in less than 10 secs with some bad luck...)<br>
<br>
Especially for the Servants you need often more than 1 Pet (not to say always) even with clicking BWS as often as possible. So I just use every Pet as far as possible.<br>
<br>
I start recasting a new Pet when the old Pet is at:<br>
30-35% when fighting servants<br>
20% when fighting worshippers<br>
never when fighting Warders (Pet usually loses less than 20% HPs here...)<br>
for all the named Tro Jegs I usually start between 30 and 40%.<br>
<br>
<br>
Now, when I started the whole chaining I was specialized in Evocation. And I noticed the *huge* improvement even then.(Got enshrouded Veil , which decreased casting costs already)<br>
<br>
After I did that for most of a level (I think late 56/early 57) I went to SolRo and changed my specialisation. Meanwhile I'm up to 150 again...<br>
<br>
I have to say the effect of specilisation isnt all that huge.<br>
The only difference i mention now is that I can cast an additional nuke now and then, but thats too seldom to really make a huge difference... <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.euphorion.org/sig/euph_new2.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=liffthemage>Liff the Mage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#333333>(12/2/02 7:47:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=311.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: JP Gnolls</span><hr size=1> Elonia asked how I fight in the caves, I agree with Shlakor's methods with one difference.  I like to fight my way in.<br>
<br>
The reason is I normally get to kill the wandering gnolls before they get to aggro me.  I just got run 3, and I am happy to say that the gnolls can't keep up with me any longer.  Before run 3 I would recomend SoW potions and keeping SoW up at most times.<br>
<br>
The 49 Earth pet is what I like to use (I like 51 or 57 better, but only use these when I have KEI), with Shock of Steel thrown in at the end.  Seems to be very mana efficient as the gnoll warriors have (I think) 4 to 6 khps, and this kills the gnoll by me using about 650 or so mana, while I get to med during the fight.  <br>
<br>
At 57 with KEI I get a little more than 1 blue xp per hour or so.  The rooms I like to hunt in are the 'bean' shaped room that is about in the middle of the cave complex, and the 3rd room in if you take all left turns from the entrance.  More spawns in the 'bean' room, more wanders in the other, but I don't really have a preference between the two.  I have not tried the drop off room yet.  Even with KEI, I still reclaim pets every now and then.<br>
<br>
At 56 when I first tried hunting here, I didn't do well, and quit trying.  I came back at 57 thinking the new pet would make all the difference, but it doesn't, as I don't normally use it now.  I think this could be done at level 56 as the new DS is at this level, and the extra 8 points helps lots.  A better player than myself could do this at the low 50's if they had SoW or run 3 as you will get chased out of the caves from time to time.<br>
<br>
I have been in groups in here, but the xp slows, so I don't do that anymore.  Unless the other player is a necro.  IMHO, they are the best player to team with a mage.<br>
<br>
I'll be here till 58, and I do think that unless you are chain casting, there isn't much reason to fight here.  Again my opinion, the mobs have too many hps to nuke em down.  I am sure others feel differently though, so use whatever works best for you.<br>
<br>
Sorry for the rambling post =).<br>
<br>
